Wash and dry produce. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}. Trim 
and quarter @zucchini{1} lengthwise; slice crosswise into ½-inch-thick 
quarter-moons. Halve @grape tomatoes{4%ounce}. Quarter @lemon{1}. Roughly 
chop @parsley{¼%ounce}. Dice @fresh mozzarella{4%ounce} into ½-inch pieces.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a #small pot{} over 
medium-high heat. Add half the garlic and a big pinch of @salt{}; cook, 
stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add @Israeli couscous{2.5%ounce}, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, and 
¾ cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings). Bring to a boil, then reduce 
to a low simmer and cover. Cook until couscous is tender, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While couscous cooks, heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over 
medium-high heat. Add zucchini and half the @Italian seasoning{1%tablespoon} 
(all for 4 servings); cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and 
softened, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Add tomatoes and remaining garlic; cook, stirring, until tomatoes are 
softened and garlic is fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Remove from heat and season with salt and @pepper{}.

Fluff couscous with a #fork{}; stir in a squeeze of lemon juice and 
season with salt and pepper if needed. Stir in half the veggies and 
half the parsley.

> TIP: Stir in 1 TBSP butter for a richer flavor!

Divide couscous between #bowls{2}. Top with remaining veggies, then top 
with mozzarella. Sprinkle with @sliced almonds{½%ounce}, remaining 
parsley, and as many @?chili flakes{1%teaspoon} as you like. Drizzle each 
bowl with ½ tsp @olive oil{1%teaspoon} and serve with remaining lemon 
wedges on the side.